{"change_summary":"Made milestone completion replay-safe and invariant-preserving. `TaskRunLineagePort::update_task_run` now returns the canonical finalized entry and accepts idempotent replays of the same terminal payload, the milestone service rebuilds snapshot progress/active state from lineage before persisting so completed snapshots no longer remain `active` without an `active_bead`, and completion journal writes are deduplicated so retrying after a partial failure repairs drift without double-counting. Added regression coverage for replayed completion repair and post-completion snapshot validity.","outstanding_risks":["Milestone completion still spans separate lineage, snapshot, and journal files without a cross-file transaction, so a crash can leave snapshot or journal state temporarily behind `task-runs.ndjson` until the same completion is replayed."],"steps":[{"description":"Updated the task-run lineage port and filesystem adapter so completion updates return the finalized row, backfill missing optional metadata on matching terminal replays, and still reject conflicting duplicate finalizations.","order":0,"status":"completed"},{"description":"Reworked milestone completion to reconcile snapshot counters and active/status fields from canonical lineage state, validate snapshot semantics before writes, and skip re-appending an already-recorded completion journal event.","order":1,"status":"completed"},{"description":"Extended milestone_record tests to cover Ready-after-completion semantics and retrying a completion after a journal write failure, then reran formatting, milestone tests, and clippy.","order":2,"status":"completed"}],"validation_evidence":["`cargo fmt --all` completed successfully.","`cargo test --lib contexts::milestone_record` passed with 68 tests.","`cargo clippy -- -D warnings` completed successfully."]}